Package com.fluidops.iwb.api.editor

RDF Triple Editor.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
TripleEditorSource Interface that models data source for the Triple editor.
TripleEditorSourceBNode Interface for a blank node (BNode) source.
TripleEditorSourceLiteral Literal source interface.
TripleEditorSourceURI  
Validation Interface for any string based validation in the Information Workbench.
 

Class Summary
TripleEditorConstants Constant definitions.
TripleEditorPropertyInfo Models information about resource properties.
TripleEditorSourceBNodeImpl Triple editor source for blank nodes retrieving the outgoing and optionally the incoming statements (all at once).
TripleEditorSourceFactory Factory for triple editor source instances.
TripleEditorSourceLiteralImpl  
TripleEditorSourceLoadAtOnceBase<T> Base class implementation for all TripleEditorSources that retrieve all data at once for the given value.
TripleEditorSourceURIImpl Triple editor source for URI resources which retrieves the outgoing and optionally the incoming statements.
TripleEditorSourceURIOnDemand Triple editor source reloading URIs on demand.
TripleEditorStatement This interface models a semantic statement - subject, predicate, object, context - used by the Triple Editor.
 

Enum Summary
Datatype Supported datatypes in the Information Workbench.
DatatypeValidation This class provides standard validators for known types, e.g. the most important XML schema types as defined in http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema11-2/ This enumeration can be used for type based evaluation, i.e. if the target type of some output is known.
